sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Service as modelmesh-serving Service<br/>8008/TCP HTTP or 8033/TCP gRPC
    participant RESTProxy as REST Proxy<br/>8008/TCP HTTP
    participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh Container<br/>8033/TCP gRPC
    participant ETCD as ETCD<br/>2379/TCP HTTP/gRPC
    participant Runtime as Model Runtime<br/>UDS or 8001/TCP gRPC
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Model Serving Request (REST)
    Client->>Service: POST /v2/models/{model}/infer<br/>HTTP (no encryption)<br/>Optional auth
    Service->>RESTProxy: Forward request<br/>HTTP
    RESTProxy->>ModelMesh: Translate to gRPC<br/>8033/TCP
    ModelMesh->>ETCD: Query model metadata<br/>2379/TCP (optional TLS)
    ETCD-->>ModelMesh: Model location
    ModelMesh->>Runtime: Inference request<br/>gRPC (UDS or 8001/TCP)
    Runtime-->>ModelMesh: Prediction result
    ModelMesh-->>RESTProxy: gRPC response
    RESTProxy-->>Service: HTTP response
    Service-->>Client: JSON prediction

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: Model Serving Request (gRPC - Direct)
    Client->>Service: gRPC ModelInfer<br/>8033/TCP (no encryption)
    Service->>ModelMesh: Forward gRPC request
    ModelMesh->>ETCD: Query model metadata<br/>Optional TLS
    ETCD-->>ModelMesh: Model info
    ModelMesh->>Runtime: Inference via gRPC
    Runtime-->>ModelMesh: Result
    ModelMesh-->>Service: gRPC response
    Service-->>Client: gRPC result

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 3: Model Loading from Storage
    participant User as User/kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as modelmesh-controller
    participant Puller as Storage Puller<br/>Init Container

    User->>K8sAPI: Create InferenceService<br/>HTTPS/TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment<br/>HTTPS/TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>Puller: Start init container
    Puller->>K8sAPI: Read storage-config Secret<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Puller->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>AWS Signature V4
    S3-->>Puller: Model files
    Note over Puller,Runtime: Shared volume (filesystem)
    Puller-->>Runtime: Model ready on shared volume
    Runtime->>Runtime: Load model into memory
